params.currencyRef: Id of currency collateral is denominated in

addERC1155NFTCurrency(address).details: Note that no tokenId is required -- since we know the count to be 1, the structures that reference this currency can use their field to specify the tokenId.

params.location: address of ERC1155 contract being added

addERC1155TokenCurrency(address,uint256).details: TokenId is required because structures that reference this currency are only able to specify one field -- the amount, and so the tokenId must be constant and specified here

params.location: address of the ERC1155 contract being added
params.tokenId: specific tokenId to associate with this ERC1155 currency listing.

params.location: address of the ERC20 contract being added

addERC721Currency(address).details: Add a new currency of type ERC721

params.location: address of the ERC721 contract being added

callBond(uint256).details: Can only be performed by token owner or authorized operator.

params.id: Id of bond to check for default

forgiveBond(uint256).details: Can only be performed by token owner or authorized operator.

returns._0: Bond As the expanded bond datastructure at given id

mintBond(bytes32,bytes32).details: Minter field must correspond to message sender!

params.alp: Alpha bytes to append, as generated by library
params.bet: Beta bytes to append, as generated by library

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.details: Handler function that get's called on any ERC1155 transfer to this function -- accepts only transfers initiated by itself.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Handler function that get's called on any ERC721 transfer to this function -- accepts only transfers initiated by itself.

safeBatchReleaseCollaterals(uint256[],ad.details: Method is optimized to memoize the 'previous' bond and currency used. If possible, sort incoming lists by bondIds and by related currencyIds.

params.bondIds: Integer array of bondIds to release collateral for
params.data: bytes to forward with each transfer
params.to: address to direct all collaterals to

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers `tokenId` token from `from` to `to`, checking first that contract recipients are aware of the ERC721 protocol to prevent tokens from being forever locked. `_data` is additional data, it has no specified format and it is sent in call to `to`. This internal function is equivalent to {safeTransferFrom}, and can be used to e.g. implement alternative mechanisms to perform token transfer, such as signature-based. Requirements: - `from` cannot be the zero address. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - `tokenId` token must exist and be owned by `from`. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

serviceBond(uint256,address,uint256,byte.details: For ether transactions, from and value still have to match or exceed the ether sent and the message sender. Note that call data will only get forwarded for supporting currencies

params.data: Additonal bytes to send with the transaction
params.from: Account address to take value from
params.value: Either the amount to apply to the bond, or the NFT id to transfer as service payment

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Approve `operator` to operate on all of `owner` tokens Emits a {ApprovalForAll} event.
